node.title: Sixth case of Omicron variant of COVID-19 confirmed in NSW
node.alt: A passenger walks next to a departures sign at Sydney International Airport
node.description: A returned traveller who recently visited southern Africa is found to have the Omicron variant after flying into Sydney on a flight from Doha.Â
node.content:
["NSW Health has confirmed a sixth returned traveller in the state has tested positive for the Omicron COVID-19 variant of concern.", "A man in his 40s is isolating in Sydney's west after developing mild symptoms following his arrival\u00a0on a flight QR908 from Doha last Thursday.", "The traveller tested positive to COVID-19 yesterday.", "It's been revealed the man visited Chemist Warehouse, at The Grove in Liverpool on Monday between 8:10pm and 8:20pm.", "Anyone who was in the chemist at the same time is considered a casual contact and must get tested immediately and isolate until they get a negative result.", "This is the second case of the Omicron variant connected to the Doha flight.", "Investigations are continuing into three other COVID-19 cases among passengers on the same flight.", "At least six people on board were known to\u00a0 have visited southern Africa in the previous fortnight.", "NSW Health said there was no evidence that transmission had occurred on the flight.", "However, every person on that\u00a0flight is considered to be a close contact and is advised to get tested immediately and isolate for 14 days.", "Health authorities are\u00a0attempting to contact all passengers and flight crew to advise them of the requirements. .", "More to follow.", "", "
Heavily mutated Omicron variant puts scientist on alert
"]
